0–":"about 1580–Deceased","1580–Male":"1580–Deceased","1580–Female":"1580–Deceased","1603–Female":"1603–Deceased","1550–Male":"1550–Deceased","1550–Female":"1550–Deceased","ABT 1580":"about 1580","1550":"1550","1580":"1580","1603":"1603","Raon-L'Étape,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-l'Étape, Vosges, Lorraine, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"COLIN","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Alfredo, Francisco, Jesus, Ricardo, Alberto, Angel, Arturo, Eduardo, Esteban, Faustino.  French Alexandre, Andre, Armand, Georges, Henri, Jean Claude, Jean-Michel, Laurette, Lucien, Marcel, Patrice, Pierre.","French, Walloon, and Breton: from a French shortened pet form of the personal name   Nicolas   (see   Nicholas  ). This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium.","English: from the personal name <i>Colin</i>, a diminutive of <i>Col</i>, itself a pet form of   Nicholas  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Collin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Marcel, Leonide, Andre, Armand, Camille, Emile, Fernand, Firmin, Francois, Ghislaine, Normand.","English, French, Walloon, and Breton: variant of   Colin  . This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium.","German: variant of   Kollin   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]},{"name":"Collins","meanings":["English: variant of   Colin  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish and Manx: shortened Anglicized from <b>Ó Coileáin</b>, compare   Cullen  , or in Man or west Ulster shortened from <b>Mac Coileáin</b>, compare   McQuillan   and   McCallion  . The genitival <i>-s</i> is a local addition to   Collin   and variants after the surname was Anglicized.","Americanized form of French   Colin   or   Collin   and also   Collette  ."]},{"name":"Collinson","meanings":["English (northern England and Lincolnshire): patronymic from the Middle English personal name   Colin   + <i>son</i>."]},{"name":"Collen","meanings":["English (Cambridgeshire): variant of   Colin  ."]},{"name":"Colan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Anselmo, Carlos, Juan, Luis, Marcos, Margarita, Pablo, Roberto.","English: probably an altered form of   Colin  .","Hispanic (mainly Peru; <b>Colán</b>): unexplained."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Alberto, Angelito, Emilio, Fernando, Francisco, Manuel, Mario, Ricardo, Rodolfo, Ruben, Alfredo, Angel.  French Luc, Pierre, Andre, Georges, Jacques, Marcellin, Yves, Adrien, Alain, Camille, Celina, Dominique.","Spanish (<b>Nicolás</b>), French, Walloon, Breton, and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from the personal name <i>Nicolás</i> (Spanish), <i>Nicolas</i> (French, Breton), from Greek <i>Nikolaos</i> (see   Nicholas  ). In France, this surname is most common in Brittany.","English (southern England and Glamorgan): variant of   Nicholas  ."]}]},{"name":"Pierre","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From New Testament Greek.  See  <b>Peter</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peter","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Pierre COLIN was born about 1580, his father, Demenge Colin, was 31 and his mother, Marguerite BERNIER, was 32. He had at least 1 daughter with Agnès Cuvelier."},"et":{"ABT 1580–":"umbes 1580–Surnud","1580–Male":"1580–Surnud","1580–Female":"1580–Surnud","1603–Female":"1603–Surnud","1550–Male":"1550–Surnud","1550–Female":"1550–Surnud","ABT 1580":"umbes 1580","1550":"1550","1580":"1580","1603":"1603","Raon-L'Étape,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-l'Étape, Vosges, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1580–":"noin 1580–Kuollut","1580–Male":"1580–Kuollut","1580–Female":"1580–Kuollut","1603–Female":"1603–Kuollut","1550–Male":"1550–Kuollut","1550–Female":"1550–Kuollut","ABT 1580":"noin 1580","1550":"1550","1580":"1580","1603":"1603","Raon-L'Étape,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-l'Étape, Vosges, Lorraine, Ranska"},"fr":{"ABT 1580–":"environ 1580–Décédé","1580–Male":"1580–Décédé","1580–Female":"1580–Décédée","1603–Female":"1603–Décédée","1550–Male":"1550–Décédé","1550–Female":"1550–Décédée","ABT 1580":"environ 1580","1550":"1550","1580":"1580","1603":"1603","Raon-L'Étape,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-l'Étape, Vosges, Lorraine, France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Pierre COLIN est né environ 1580, son père, Demenge Colin, avait 31 ans et sa mère, Marguerite BERNIER, avait 32 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Agnès Cuvelier."},"de":{"ABT 1580–":"um 1580–Verstorben","1580–Male":"1580–Verstorben","1580–Female":"1580–Verstorben","1603–Female":"1603–Verstorben","1550–Male":"1550–Verstorben","1550–Female":"1550–Verstorben","ABT 1580":"um 1580","1550":"1550","1580":"1580","1603":"1603","Raon-L'Étape,88110,Vosges,Grand Est,FRANCE,":"Raon-l'Étape, Vosges, Lothringen, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Als Pierre COLIN um 1580 geboren wurde, war sein Vater Demenge Colin 31 und seine Mutter Marguerite BERNIER 32. Er hatte mit Agnès Cuvelier mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"ABT 1580–":"about 1580–Desede","1580–Male":"1580–Desede","1580–Female":"1580–Desede","1603–Female":"1603–Desede","1550–Male":"1550–Desede","